{
  "stem": "1917.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Mother was up front, the four girls between them, and my father was at the end.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "When we reached the gate of the apple orchard, we were surrounded by the Nazis.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "We turned back.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And that was the only effort they ever tried.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "By-- by '43, it was too late.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "If they would have left maybe in '41-- I was very, very angry with my parents for a very long time.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "I do realize that they did the best they could.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And nobody can do better than their best.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "I wish that they would have seen the tragedy coming the way I saw it coming.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "Because I could tell, [? scent ?], day in, day out, things were getting more difficult.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "One of the interesting things from how we learned in that small village what was going on-- in 1941, my father bought a radio-- battery-operated radio.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And what they would do-- they would close the door when it was news time, and they would listen to the news.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "Well, as I said, I was always very curious.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And I put my ears to the door, because I wanted to know whar was-- what they were listening to that was so important.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And I could hear reports from Hitler.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And he was yelling on the radio that he was going to rule the world, and he was going to kill all the Jews.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And so I asked my parents about it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And they said, well, don't worry.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "They are not going to come here.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "That is far away.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "That's happening in Germany.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "You don't have anything to worry about.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
